          "date": "2013-01-12 01:30:31.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-1199 build: Overhaul spec file and rpm build process",
        "message": "LU-1199 build: Overhaul spec file and rpm build process\n\n- Make it possible to override Requires and BuildRequires at\n  rpmbuild time.\n- Use rpmbuild --with/--without parameters.\n- Group configuration settings for each distro into\n  clear sections at the top of the spec file, rather than\n  strewn throughout the file.\n- Eliminate all configure_args parsing.  Instead explicitly\n  pass arguments to rpmbuild as needed.\n- Improve release string handling.  No more stray underscores\n  in source rpm name!\n- Don't include kernel string in version of source rpm.\n- \"make rpms\" now employs \"make src\" to first build the\n  source rpm.  This will help enforce disipline in keeping\n  the source rpm rebuildable.\n\nChange-Id: Id0612ade9f170d84518f01d4e8de654a7ba8af88\nSigned-off-by: Christopher J. Morrone <morrone2@llnl.gov>\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
